\"/assets/faces/normal/banghead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\nLink<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/tongue.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/tongue.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/tongue.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> 咁搞笑！！</blockquote><br />\n<br />\n有幾個hacker講既都值得聽"},{"pid":"d20715adbb3e183fa6fbc84c2c5b8651e0db1cad","tid":382372,"uid":120537,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-09-03T16:57:01.000Z","msg":"<blockquote>細個都覺得 睇完 TED Talks 自己智力值增加50%<br />\n但大左 就覺得呢種 Talk mostly simplified everything<br />\n<br />\n絕大部份TED 只可以當做入門, <br />\n但如果睇完TED 就覺得自己識,反而仲衰過你唔睇<br />\n小心服用啦大家<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\n送一個屌TED Talk 既TED Talk比大家<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Yo5cKRmJaf0\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DYo5cKRmJaf0&d=aTI0xW5AaQCkVNzvabHkVE%2FDJpISyAq9ELy6OyFxwDc%3D&h=3615bd7c\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Yo5cKRmJaf0</a></blockquote><br />\n<br />\n佢真係幾cynical，一嚟就屌Malcom Gladwell <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\n不過你睇下TED成幾千蚊美金張飛就知啲talk其實唔係畀我哋聽，<br />\n係畀啲有錢入場嘅人聽完去科水，或者喺自己領域度發揮影響力<br />\n所以大部分嘅talk其實都係無咁露骨嘅elevator pitch<br />\n<br />\n我都認同係好多人聽完個TED talk或者睇完半本書就突然變咗專家， <br />\n然後終日就打飛機/圍爐自己幾intellectual幾關心個世界，但實質一啲都改變到個世界 <br />\n咁但係on9仔就點都實有架啦<br />\n但同一班人入面有on9仔都有未來嘅太空人科學家etc<br />\n<br />\n同埋佢嗰種匿埋喺個lab做研究就好重要<br />\n而inspire大眾就係mk behavior嗰種態度有少少大龜嘅酸味 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/frown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"a20aeced5f2a9a9327fa4a07ec1494f65b46ad0a","tid":382372,"uid":29628,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-09-03T17:08:57.000Z","msg":"<blockquote><blockquote><blockquote>睇過一個小偷講talk，講分散注意力<br />\n請咗條友上台，然後瘋狂偷佢野<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/banghead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\nLink<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/tongue.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/tongue.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/tongue.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> 咁搞笑！！</blockquote><br />\n<br />\n有幾個hacker講既都值得聽</blockquote><br />\n<a href=\"https://youtu.be/efw9kX0v4vU\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fyoutu.be%2Fefw9kX0v4vU&d=aTI0xW5AaQCkVNzvabHkVE%2FDJpISyAq9ELy6OyFxwDc%3D&h=e8f80787\" target=\"_blank\">https://youtu.be/efw9kX0v4vU</a>"},{"pid":"5cc39c683a5cba4dcb3594edbc7b3853b3e752a0","tid":382372,"uid":48680,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-09-03T17:12:05.000Z","msg":"<blockquote><blockquote>細個都覺得 睇完 TED Talks 自己智力值增加50%<br />\n但大左 就覺得呢種 Talk mostly simplified everything<br />\n<br />\n絕大部份TED 只可以當做入門, <br />\n但如果睇完TED 就覺得自己識,反而仲衰過你唔睇<br />\n小心服用啦大家<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\n送一個屌TED Talk 既TED Talk比大家<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Yo5cKRmJaf0\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DYo5cKRmJaf0&d=aTI0xW5AaQCkVNzvabHkVE%2FDJpISyAq9ELy6OyFxwDc%3D&h=3615bd7c\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Yo5cKRmJaf0</a></blockquote><br />\n<br />\n佢真係幾cynical，一嚟就屌Malcom Gladwell <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\n不過你睇下TED成幾千蚊美金張飛就知啲talk其實唔係畀我哋聽，<br />\n係畀啲有錢入場嘅人聽完去科水，或者喺自己領域度發揮影響力<br />\n所以大部分嘅talk其實都係無咁露骨嘅elevator pitch<br />\n<br />\n我都認同係好多人聽完個TED talk或者睇完半本書就突然變咗專家， <br />\n然後終日就打飛機/圍爐自己幾intellectual幾關心個世界，但實質一啲都改變到個世界 <br />\n咁但係on9仔就點都實有架啦<br />\n但同一班人入面有on9仔都有未來嘅太空人科學家etc<br />\n<br />\n同埋佢嗰種匿埋喺個lab做研究就好重要<br />\n而inspire大眾就係mk behavior嗰種態度有少少大龜嘅酸味 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/frown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\n我自已咁諗啦<br />\n呢種cynical 唔係烏大龜 式o個種<br />\n較具理性 警世意味較重<br />\n<br />\n我都唔全盤認同佢諗法<br />\n但我同意呢d talk要多d 深入省思<br />\n小d flashy &quot;inspiration&quot; , <br />\n因此我會係呢個post推介呢個talk<br />\n當係 平衡下 等個post多元化少少lor<img src=\"/assets